text: Stjørdal is a municipality in Trøndelag county, Norway. The administrative centre of the municipality is the town of Stjørdal, also called Stjørdalshalsen. Other villages include Hegra, Hell, Kvithammer, Prestmoen and Skatval. In 2022, 24,287 people lived there. ==Related pages== *List of mayors in Norway that are elected until 2027 == Other websites == * Official website Category:Municipalities of Trøndelag
